Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}; roughly chop leaves. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with paper towels; season all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to pot. Cook until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

While pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add kale and a splash of water. Cook until kale is wilted and very tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> TIP: If necessary, cook kale in batches.

Stir in garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to a #plate{}.

Heat another drizzle of olive oil in pan used for kale over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Return kale to pan with chicken and reduce heat to medium low. Add @cream sauce base{4%ounce}.

> TIP: Cut top off carton to open fully; transfer contents, using a spoon or spatula to scrape sauce from carton sides.

Stir in @cream cheese{2%tablespoon} and ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water. Bring to a simmer and cook until sauce is combined and thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add drained spaghetti and @butter{1%tablespoon} to pan with sauce; toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper. If needed, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide pasta between #bowls{}, top with @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, and serve.